    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hi @aymeric-giraudet\r\nI understand your point of view. Maybe this escape feature could be configurable (opt-in or opt-out) to avoid duplicating the connectToggleFilter code ?\r\n\r\nAs for the `Configure` solution we tried it but we encounter the following behavior.\r\nImagine a page with a toggleRefinement where `on` value is '5'.\r\nOff value is not set because negative filter is not possible, so we instantiate a `Configure` node that take the negative filter in properties when `isRefined = false`.\r\n\r\n1. User arrive on the page, checkbox is not checked, query is sent with negative filter from `Configure`\r\n2. User check the box, toggleRefinement `refine` is executed but `Configure` will only dismount on next rerender.\r\nSo, query is sent with both `on` and `off` value.\r\n3. Configure node is dismounted from the DOM, another query is sent with `on` value only\r\n\r\nThis result is two query sent when checkbox is checked, instead of one.",
